benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC13, TC14, TC16, TC18, TC19, TC20, TC21, TC22, TC24, TC25, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31) ensure successful uploads with valid XML and headers.
Invalid Payload: Scenarios TC08, TC18, TC23, TC30 cover malformed, corrupted, or whitespace-only XML payloads.
Missing/Invalid Headers: TC06, TC07 cover missing or empty required headers.
Extra Headers: TC11 tests handling of unexpected headers.
Large Payloads: TC12 and TC27 test large XML payloads and whitespace-heavy XML.
Duplicate Version: TC25 addresses duplicate catalog versions.
Security: TC17 tests malicious content, and TC14 covers authentication issues.
Performance: TC19 and TC20 evaluate system under load and concurrency.
Regression & Compatibility: TC21 and TC22 ensure bug fixes and backward compatibility.
Encoding & Special Content: TC24, TC29 test unicode, different encodings, comments, and CDATA sections.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios simulate rapid or excessive requests.
Timeouts & Network Failures: No tests for network interruptions or backend unavailability.
Response Content Validation: No detailed checks on response body content beyond status codes.
Edge Cases: Limited testing of boundary values for fields or extremely large XMLs beyond size.
Accessibility: No tests for accessibility features or assistive technology compatibility.
recommendations: Add tests for authorization failures (missing/invalid tokens).
Include scenarios verifying cache headers and caching behavior.
Implement rate limiting and request throttling tests.
Simulate network failures and backend downtime to test resilience.
Enhance response validation to check response body content and structure.
Test boundary values and maximum sizes for XML payloads.
Add accessibility and usability tests for assistive technology compatibility.
